---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy — Spark Commit"
  description="What data Spark Commit collects, and where it goes. Spoiler: nothing leaves your machine."
>
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20 lg:py-28">
    <a
      href="/"
      class="text-sm text-ink-900/60 hover:text-sparkle dark:text-ink-50/60">← Back to home</a
    >

    <h1 class="mt-6 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">Privacy</h1>

    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-ink-900/60 dark:text-ink-50/60">Last updated: 18 April 2026.</p>

    <div class="prose-spark mt-10 space-y-6 text-base text-ink-900 dark:text-ink-50">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sparkle">This website</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink-900/80 dark:text-ink-50/80">
          sparkcommit.com is a static site. It sets no cookies, runs no analytics, loads no
          third-party trackers. Your IP address is visible to the hosting provider
          (Cloudflare Pages) for the duration of serving a request and isn't stored by this
          site.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sparkle">The extension</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink-900/80 dark:text-ink-50/80">
          Spark Commit itself makes no network connections. It spawns the Claude CLI process
          locally, which then communicates with Anthropic's API under <em>your</em> own account
          — the same network path you would use by running <code
            class="font-mono text-sm">claude</code
          > in a terminal yourself. The extension never has or sees your API key.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink-900/80 dark:text-ink-50/80">
          Spark Commit adds no proxies, no telemetry, no crash reports, no error traces and no
          metadata of its own. Your staged diff — the one thing it handles — goes into the CLI
          call and nowhere else.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sparkle">Anthropic's side</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink-900/80 dark:text-ink-50/80">
          The Claude CLI handles data according to <a
            href="https://www.anthropic.com/legal/privacy"
            class="underline decoration-sparkle decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-sparkle"
            >Anthropic's privacy policy</a
          >. Spark Commit has no visibility into or influence over that path — it's the same
          path you'd use by typing <code class="font-mono text-sm">claude</code> in your
          terminal yourself.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sparkle">If this ever changes</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink-900/80 dark:text-ink-50/80">
          If analytics, crash reports, or any form of telemetry are ever added, the
          introduction will be documented here, announced in the <a
            href="https://github.com/jakubburkiewicz/spark-commit/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md"
            class="underline decoration-sparkle decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-sparkle"
            >CHANGELOG</a
          > and visible in git history of both the extension and this site. You can always
          audit the current state — the source is open.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-sparkle">Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink-900/80 dark:text-ink-50/80">
          Privacy concerns, corrections, questions — open an issue on <a
            href="https://github.com/jakubburkiewicz/spark-commit/issues"
            class="underline decoration-sparkle decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-sparkle"
            >GitHub</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
